User Bookings Project

This project provides a simple frontend and backend setup to fetch and display user booked events, combining separate event date and time fields for correct display.
___________________________________

Features

    Fetch user bookings via API

    Populate event details with date and time

    Display bookings in a user-friendly list

    Basic error handling
_____________________________________

Prerequisites

    Node.js v14 or later

    MongoDB instance running locally or remotely

    NPM (comes with Node.js)
_____________________________________

Backend Setup

    Clone the repository:

    git clone https://github.com/a-amrashraf/ATC_01113736259.git
    cd Areeb-Task

    Install dependencies:

    npm install

    Configure environment variables

    Create a .env file in the project root with the following variables:

    MONGODB_URI="mongodb://localhost:27017/Event_managment"
    PORT=5000
    JWT_SECRET=58b8c4677516fb625eb91a1940bb867c9ee3d0e9eb5d51d39981120752e78a49

    Start the backend server:

    npm start

    The API will be available at http://localhost:5000